图片来源：推特记者 ：肖恩“ 美国已发现四例感染路径未明的疑似社区传播案例，都来自西岸。
Source: Twitter reporter Shawn: "The United States has identified four suspected cases of community transmission with unclear infection paths, all from the West Bank.
美国媒体称，这可能意味着美国西岸存在新冠病毒“社区传播”的可能。
US media say this could mean there is a "community spread" of the new cap virus in the West Bank.
”在中国境外新冠肺炎确诊病例突破6000人的同时，美澳两国陆续出现首例死亡病例，而美国疫情在社区传播的风险正在加大。
"While more than 6,000 new cases of pneumonia have been confirmed outside China, the United States and Australia are seeing their first cases of death and the risk of spreading the disease in their communities is increasing.
华盛顿州一家首现医护人员感染的医护中心有超过50人出现疑似症状，该州已进入紧急状态。
A state of emergency has been declared in Washington state, where more than 50 people are suspected to be suffering from the infection.
当地时间3月1日上午，澳大利亚西澳州出现首例新冠肺炎死亡病例。
The Australian state of Western Australia reported its first case of death from pneumonia on March 1, local time.
西澳州首席卫生官员罗伯特森（Andrew Robertson）在新闻发布会上通报称，死者是一名78岁的男性，是“钻石公主”号邮轮上的乘客，两周前跟随该国撤侨包机回国，约九至十天前在隔离中心确诊。
Andrew Robertson, WA's chief health officer, told a news conference that the deceased was a 78-year-old man, a passenger on board the MV Princess Diamond, who had returned from chartered flights with the country two weeks ago and was diagnosed at the quarantine centre about nine to ten days ago.
他的妻子也已确诊感染，目前在医院隔离治疗。
His wife has also been diagnosed with the infection and is being treated in isolation in hospital.
罗伯特森表示，目前澳大利亚仍未出现社区传播现象。
There is still no community transmission in Australia, Robertson said.
澳大利亚内政部长则在1日表示，不可能对所有受到新冠肺炎疫情影响的国家采取入境限制。
Australia's interior minister said on Monday that it would not be possible to impose entry restrictions on all countries affected by the outbreak.
澳大利亚已经禁止曾经到过伊朗的旅客入境，但未对连日来确诊人数激增的韩国作出限制。
Australia has banned visitors who have been to Iran, but has imposed no restrictions on South Korea, which has seen a surge in the number of confirmed cases over the past few days.
美国的情况似乎更为严峻。
The situation in the United States seems even more serious.
2月29日，华盛顿州金郡卫生官员达钦（Jeffrey Duchin）通报称，美国一名感染新冠病毒的患者死亡，这是该国首例死亡病例。
On February 29, Jeffrey Duchin, a health official in Kingshire, Washington, reported the death of a person infected with the new crown virus, the country's first case of death.
死者是一名50多岁的男性，本身患有基础疾病。
The deceased was a man in his fifties who had a basic illness of his own.
当地政府在28日才收到患者的相关信息，并于29日宣布其核酸检测结果推定阳性。
The local government received information about the patient only on the 28th, and announced on the 29th, its nucleic acid test results are presumed positive.
美国疾控中心（CDC）主任拉德菲尔德（Robert Redfield）表示，目前没有证据指明该患者曾与新冠肺炎确诊患者有接触或有危险地区旅行史，因此他可能是通过社区传播感染。
Robert Redfield, director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in the United States, said there was no evidence that the patient had been in contact with a confirmed Crowne Pneumonia patient or had a travel history in a dangerous area, and that he might therefore have transmitted the infection through the community.
截至目前美国已发现四例感染路径未明的疑似社区传播案例，分别来自西岸的加州、俄勒冈州和华盛顿州。
So far, four cases of suspected community transmission with unclear infection paths have been identified in the United States, from the West Bank states of California, Oregon and Washington.
美国媒体称，这可能意味着美国西岸或存在新冠肺炎“社区传播”的可能。
US media say this could mean there is a possibility of "community transmission" of pneumonia in the West Bank.
美国总统特朗普29日下午在白宫举行新闻发布会，证实首例死亡病例的消息，并称该患者本身就属于“高风险”的患者。
US President Trump 29 afternoon at the White House press conference to confirm the news of the first case of death, and said the patient itself is a "high-risk" patients.
他表示，虽然美国确诊病例数量很可能继续增加，但“健康的人”都能够彻底治愈。
While the number of confirmed cases in the US is likely to continue to rise, "healthy people" can all be cured, he said.
特朗普说，无论接下来情况如何，都已做好准备，并要求媒体、政客及其他相关人士不要煽动恐慌，因为没有理由恐慌。
Trump says whatever happens next is ready, and asks the media, politicians, and others concerned not to foment panic, because there is no reason to panic.
特朗普此前曾指责民主党人把病毒“政治化”，利用此次事件攻击和抹黑政府，同时还提到了“通俄门”调查和总统弹劾。
Trump has previously accused Democrats of "politicizing" the virus, using the incident to attack and discredit the government, as well as referring to the "Tungman" investigation and the impeachment of the president.
特朗普指出，白宫正在考虑继续收紧旅行限制措施，极有可能关闭南部边境，但随后又称墨西哥边境“目前还没大问题”。
Trump has pointed out that the White House is considering further tightening of travel restrictions, most likely closing the southern border, but later calling the Mexican border "not a big problem at the moment."
美国副总统彭斯在记者会上宣布，将扩大对伊朗旅行禁令，过去14天有过伊朗旅行史的外国人将被拒绝入境美国。
Vice President Burns announced at a news conference that the travel ban on Iran would be expanded and that foreigners with a history of travel to Iran over the past 14 days would be denied entry into the United States.
同时，美国国务院将对意大利和韩国的旅行警告提至4级（最高级），敦促美国民众不要前往上述国家。
Meanwhile, the State Department has raised its travel warnings for Italy and South Korea to level 4, urging Americans not to travel to those countries.
美国卫生与公共服务部（HHS）部长阿扎尔（Alex Azar）表示，大部分感染新冠病毒的患者都属于轻症患者，将会在家接受隔离治疗，治疗方法类似于重感冒和和流感。
Alex Azar, secretary of the US Department of Health and Human Services (HHS), said most people infected with the new crown virus were mild cases and would be treated at home in isolation, with treatments similar to severe colds and flu.
目前，华盛顿州州长英斯利（Jay Inslee）已经宣布该州进入紧急状态，将动用政府一切必要资源，来对抗新冠病毒爆发，如果需要会出动华盛顿州国民警卫队。
At present, Washington State Governor Jay Inslee has declared a state of emergency and will use all necessary government resources to fight the New Crown Virus outbreak, if needed by the Washington State National Guard.
华盛顿州官员还在考虑取消取消公共活动的可能性。
Washington state officials are also considering the possibility of canceling public events.
包括上述死亡患者在内，该州在29日新增五例确诊病例，其中四例传播途径未明。
Including the above-mentioned deaths, the state on the 29th five new confirmed cases, four of which transmission route is unknown.
金郡有两例传播源未明的病例都与柯克兰市的一家医疗护理中心有关，分别是一名40多岁的护理人员和一名70多岁的医疗中心住客，两人都是女性。
Two cases of unknown transmission in Kincon are related to a medical care centre in Kirkland, a paramedic in his 40s and a 70-plus resident of a medical centre, both women.
前者是美国第一例医护人员感染病例，而后者病情严重。
The former is the first case of health care worker infection in the United States, while the latter is serious.
达钦称，该医疗中心内有超过50人出现呼吸道或肺炎症状，他们将接受新冠病毒检测。
Dachin said more than 50 people at the center have respiratory or pneumonia symptoms and will be tested for the virus.
医疗中心内共有108名住客和180名工作人员。
The Medical Centre has a total of 108 residents and 180 staff.
截至2月29日，美国总共有70人在新冠病毒核酸检测中呈阳性，或推定阳性，其中44人是“钻石公主”号邮轮乘客，3人是从中国撤离的美国人，另有23人是在美国境内出现的病例。
As of February 29, a total of 70 people in the United States had tested positive or presumed positive for Nucleic Acid (Nucleic Acid), 44 of whom were passengers on board the MV Princess Diamond, 3 were Americans evacuated from China and 23 were cases that occurred in the United States.
推定阳性病例是在地方实验室检测中出现阳性结果，还需要CDC进行复测确认。
Presumably positive cases show positive results in local laboratory tests and require CDC to retest them.
鉴于美国国内疫情快速发展，美国食品和药品监督管理局（FDA）29日紧急下放权限，允许全美有资质的医院实验室开发并使用自己的新冠病毒感染检测手段，以提升检测速度。
The Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has delegated emergency powers to qualified hospital labs across the United States to develop and use their own means of testing for new crown virus infections to speed up detection, given the rapidly growing epidemic in the United States.
美国此前一直因检测效率低下而饱受诟病。
The United States has long been criticized for poor testing.
CDC此前承认，其研制出的第一批试剂盒存在缺陷，检测结果不准确。
CDC had previously acknowledged that the first kits it had developed were defective and that the results were inaccurate.
因此大部分实验室都只能利用现有试剂盒的前两步检测结果做出诊断，跳过出现问题的第三步。
So most laboratories can only use the first two steps of the existing kit to make a diagnosis and skip the third step of the problem.
但有美国卫生官员表示，CDC已经解决了这一问题，正向全国的实验室分发新版试剂盒。
But U.S. health officials say the CDC has solved the problem and is distributing new kits to labs across the country.
美国医疗总监（Surgeon General）亚当斯（JeromeM.Adams）则在推特上呼吁美国人民不要囤积口罩，留给有需要的人。
Jerome M. Adams, the US medical director, on Twitter called on Americans not to hoard masks and leave them to those in need.
他表示，对于普通大众来说，口罩的预防作用不大，但对医务工作者来说却是必需品。
For the general public, masks have little preventive effect, but are a necessity for health workers, he said.
拉德菲尔德则表示，虽然目前存在社区传播的风险，但美国民众无需该变原本的生活方式。
Radfield said while there was a risk of community transmission, Americans did not need to change their way of life.
卫生官员多次强调，预防新冠肺炎的方式跟预防流感无异，就是勤洗手、不要触摸口鼻以及感觉不适时避免出门。
Health officials have repeatedly stressed that the way to prevent pneumonia is to wash your hands frequently, not to touch your mouth and nose and to avoid going out when you are feeling unwell.
